Generic single-database configuration.

Please review the configuration and documentation at:
http://alembic.zzzcomputing.com/en/latest/tutorial.html

The majority of which is applicable to this template.

To run migrations, you can use the alembic command, which is installed
along with alembic:

    alembic -c alembic.ini upgrade head

To see all available commands, run:

    alembic -c alembic.ini --help

To see the current revision and available revisions:

    alembic -c alembic.ini current
    alembic -c alembic.ini history

To create a new revision:

    alembic -c alembic.ini revision -m "description of migration"

To create a new revision with autodetection of model changes:

    alembic -c alembic.ini revision --autogenerate -m "description of migration"

To upgrade to a specific revision:

    alembic -c alembic.ini upgrade <revision_id>

To downgrade to a specific revision:

    alembic -c alembic.ini downgrade <revision_id>

For more information, see the Alembic documentation.